<p>I have an XML file of below format:</p>  <pre><code> -&lt;table&gt;       &lt;A&gt;         &lt;a&gt;x&lt;/a&gt;         &lt;b&gt;y&lt;/b&gt;       &lt;/A&gt;        &lt;B&gt;        ...        ...        ....       &lt;/B&gt;        &lt;C&gt;        ...        ...        ...        &lt;/C&gt;     &lt;/table&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I want to make "A" as a root node instead of table. Is there any way to code in xsl so that the above xml looks like below?</p>  <pre><code> &lt;A a="x" b="y"&gt;       &lt;B&gt;       ...       ...       ...      &lt;/B&gt;       &lt;C&gt;       ...       ...       ...      &lt;/C&gt;      &lt;/A&gt; </code></pre>